                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12728083" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 13:12:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;While playing with Master restart, I found that it was very difficult to do since stopping the threads always seemed to stop the region servers. Also the visibility in RegionManager isn&apos;t great. So, since it&apos;s critical that a Master who lost its znode should stop managing the cluster, I make it kill itself. Someone who really needs a restart can still do it via cluster management, or we can do it cleanly for 0.21, or both.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12728169" author="stack" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 16:20:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch looks good.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, if cluster has only one master and master loses its lease in zk, previous, it just stuck around as a zombie.  Now it aborts.  I suppose that&apos;ll drive home the many-masters in a pretty effective way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12728184" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 16:37:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12728256" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 7 Jul 2009 17:54:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I forgot to handle the shutdown request, it was a test missing in process(). It is now committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
